{
  "texts": [
    "Let us close by calling upon a creative strand of science-fiction-inspired literature on democratic AI, which proposes novel ways to live with, and govern with, future Artificial Intelligence(s) (Salmi 2023).",
    "We imagine a thought experiment that we call the 'Permanent Election'.",
    "Under this scenario, new policies are directly informed by the real-time evolution of the demos' preferences-and the elections of representatives as we know them are no longer necessary.",
    "Decision-makers have a direct mandate to implement policies based on preferences aggregated by AI.",
    "Voters get to permanently elect policies, rather than politicians."
  ]
}